1
00:00:43,159 --> 00:00:44,200
Why is it so heavy?

2
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,000
What are you mumbling about?

3
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,159
If the Brigade Commander hears you,

4
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:48,200
he'll skin you alive.

5
00:00:51,439 --> 00:00:52,880
Am I really that brutal?

6
00:00:55,479 --> 00:00:56,000
Lift!

7
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:05,040
Open the coffin!

8
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:18,040
Present the bride!

9
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:24,439
Mother!

10
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:25,560
My daughter!

11
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:25,760
Mother!

12
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,920
Qiuying!

13
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:28,799
Mother!

14
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:30,560
My child!

15
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:31,400
Sister!

16
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:32,000
Mother!

17
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:32,280
Sister!

18
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,439
My child!

19
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,359
Mother!

20
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:35,959
Mother!

21
00:01:35,959 --> 00:01:36,920
Qiuying!

22
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:37,799
Mother!

23
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:39,799
My child!

24
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,439
My child!

25
00:01:58,319 --> 00:01:59,400
Shuisheng.

26
00:02:00,319 --> 00:02:01,840
Light the lamp.

27
00:02:04,079 --> 00:02:04,840
Let me do it.

28
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:10,560
Green fields, a grave of withered bones,

29
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:14,400
In the dim underworld, lost souls roam.

30
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:18,879
The ghost matchmaker binds their union,

31
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:22,199
The bride borrows flesh to pay respects.

32
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:26,080
The crimson coffin serves as her sedan,

33
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:29,840
Ghosts with blue lamps guide the way.

34
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:32,000
Close the coffin!

35
00:02:38,039 --> 00:02:41,360
The rites complete, she becomes his bride,

36
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:45,199
One less lonely grave in the living world.

37
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,439
Fill the grave!

38
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,280
My daughter!

39
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,960
Qiuying!

40
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,439
Qiuying!

41
00:02:55,439 --> 00:02:57,039
I understand now.

42
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,319
Please forgive me, won't you?

43
00:03:06,719 --> 00:03:07,439
Ceremony concluded!

44
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:08,719
Move out!

45
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,159
Sister.

46
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:14,840
Brother-in-law.

47
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:15,960
Let's go.

48
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:17,919
Stop crying.

49
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:20,879
You're breaking my heart.

50
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:27,000
Let's go.

51
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,319
Come on.

52
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:40,159
Whose grave is this?

53
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,319
Never mind whose grave it is.

54
00:03:41,319 --> 00:03:41,879
Dig!

55
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:42,800
It's so big.

56
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,879
Can the two of us really dig it up?

57
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:44,599
Hurry up!

58
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:48,840
Faster!

59
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,560
Master, let us do it.

60
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:52,879
Open it!

61
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:54,520
Come on.

62
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:55,680
Give me a hand.

63
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:56,919
Push it!

64
00:03:57,319 --> 00:03:57,800
Push!

65
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:02,159
He's awake!

66
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:03,240
Quick, quick, quick!

67
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:03,680
Lift him out!

68
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:04,560
Come on.

69
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:05,439
Shuisheng.

70
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:09,719
Pry it open, pry it open!

71
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:10,280
Hurry!

72
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,159
Xiaolian.

73
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:19,600
It's okay.

74
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,920
Can you stand up?

75
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:23,439
Hold on to me.

76
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,360
Xingbang is over here.

77
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:24,879
Hurry!

78
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:27,720
How is he?

79
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:39,279
Master.

80
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,680
What's going on here?

81
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,600
I had two coffins custom-made.

82
00:04:44,079 --> 00:04:45,040
But what if...

83
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:47,800
they didn't buy from that coffin shop?

84
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,879
Yinyang Ferry has only one coffin shop.

85
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,319
If not from there,

86
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:52,199
where else could they buy one?

87
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:55,079
I've known the owner for over a decade.

88
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,199
I trust him to handle it.

89
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:58,639
Master.

90
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:01,000
What were those pills you gave us?

91
00:05:01,879 --> 00:05:02,720
They help you sleep.

92
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,560
They also slow your breathing.

93
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:07,759
Two people in one coffin,

94
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:08,879
no matter what,

95
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,360
there wouldn't be enough air, right?

96
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:11,720
I get it now.

97
00:05:12,439 --> 00:05:13,240
It's this.

98
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,759
The eternal lamp.

99
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,439
I don't know the details,

100
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:19,519
but I know that Master

101
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:21,279
told me to swap their eternal lamps.

102
00:05:21,519 --> 00:05:22,680
So your eternal lamp must

103
00:05:22,839 --> 00:05:23,519
have a trick to it.

104
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:25,480
When refining elixirs in the past,

105
00:05:26,279 --> 00:05:28,079
we'd add a substance to the furnace.

106
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,040
It aids combustion and releases oxygen.

107
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,480
That's what this lamp does.

108
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:34,160
Master,

109
00:05:34,439 --> 00:05:35,519
you're amazing.

110
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:37,000
It's getting late.

111
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,519
Hurry.

112
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:38,759
Cover it up.

113
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,920
It's getting late.

114
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:44,600
Aunt Xiaoling,

115
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:45,879
I leave Master in your hands.

116
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,040
We'll head back to the unit now.

117
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:47,879
Alright.

118
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:48,839
Master,

119
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,439
stop fighting with Aunt Xiaoling.

120
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:51,000
Hear me?

121
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,519
As if I'd dare to.

122
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:57,879
Alright.

123
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,600
Shouldn't you be hugging Qiuying?

124
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,839
Qiuying and I have plenty of time to hug.

125
00:06:02,959 --> 00:06:03,759
Thanks, Dongsheng.

126
00:06:04,879 --> 00:06:05,399
So cheesy.

127
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:05,839
Let's go.

128
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:08,639
Master,

129
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:09,240
I'm leaving too.

130
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,199
Dongsheng,

131
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:13,199
I hope

132
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,839
you'll go with Xiaolian.

133
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:15,879
Yeah,

134
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:16,720
let's go together.

135
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:17,480
We can look out for each other.

136
00:06:17,639 --> 00:06:18,519
I won't go with Xiaolian.

137
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,000
If you won't go with her,

138
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,000
go with Shuisheng.

139
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:22,839
Alright?

140
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,879
I don't want you back with Li Chuanzhong.

141
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,439
Have you forgotten?

142
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:27,759
Li Chuanzhong did this.

143
00:06:27,759 --> 00:06:29,360
What good could you learn from him?

144
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,680
Go.

145
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,160
Go with Xiaolian, alright?

146
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:33,199
I'm not going anywhere.

147
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:34,120
Stay out of my business.

148
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,439
Say that again.

149
00:06:35,439 --> 00:06:36,240
Stay out of my business.

150
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,319
Brother,

151
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,240
still angry?

152
00:06:46,519 --> 00:06:47,279
What is it?

153
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:49,439
Then nothing.

154
00:06:50,199 --> 00:06:50,759
Actually,

155
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,000
I have another question for you.

156
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:52,959
Shoot.

157
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,199
After taking that pill,

158
00:06:55,199 --> 00:06:56,639
what happens if no one wakes you up?

159
00:06:57,879 --> 00:06:59,759
Then you'd enjoy an eternal slumber.

160
00:07:09,399 --> 00:07:09,839
Alright.

161
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:11,360
Alright.

162
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,720
I'm not a Maxim machine gun.

163
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,399
I'm spent.

164
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,399
Get out, all of you.

165
00:07:27,519 --> 00:07:28,279
Guards!

166
00:07:28,439 --> 00:07:29,040
Yes, sir!

167
00:07:35,199 --> 00:07:35,920
Reporting, Brigade Commander.

168
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,759
You must be exhausted, sir.

169
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:39,319
I say, Shuisheng...

170
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,160
Brigade Commander.

171
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:40,959
It's me, Dongsheng.

172
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,480
Oh, Dongsheng.

173
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:46,480
Where's Shuisheng?

174
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:47,519
Brigade Commander,

175
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:50,720
here you are.

176
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:00,639
What a useless fool.

177
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:03,839
Come on.

178
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:05,439
Help me to the bathroom.

179
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:05,920
Yes, sir.

180
00:08:06,839 --> 00:08:07,240
Brigade Commander,

181
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:07,879
what's wrong?

182
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,639
Don't play dumb.

183
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,279
Let me ask you something.

184
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,519
Last night,

185
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:18,680
were you outside the window

186
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:20,279
eavesdropping all night?

187
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,399
Reporting, Brigade Commander,

188
00:08:21,639 --> 00:08:23,160
last night's battle was unusually fierce.

189
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:27,680
Brigade Commander,

190
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,279
take it slow.

191
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,759
Isn't it because

192
00:08:32,399 --> 00:08:34,480
my poor son died?

193
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:35,879
Brigade Commander.

194
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,440
A hot fire burns more coal,

195
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,320
a fine woman wears out a man.

196
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:39,639
There's no field worn out by plowing,

197
00:08:39,639 --> 00:08:40,559
only oxen worked to death.

198
00:08:40,639 --> 00:08:41,240
Brigade Commander,

199
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,519
take care of your precious health.

200
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,519
You,

201
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:46,000
always full of smooth talk.

202
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,480
All right.

203
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:57,399
Shuisheng went home to get married anyway.

204
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:58,320
So,

205
00:08:58,679 --> 00:09:02,240
you'll act as Company Commander for now.

206
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,840
Thank you, Brigade Commander.

207
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,360
Master.

208
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:10,039
Aunt Xiaoling.

209
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:13,639
Look at me.

210
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:14,679
Notice anything different?

211
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:17,679
You've gotten more handsome.

212
00:09:17,679 --> 00:09:18,559
Impossible.

213
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,080
I'm already the most handsome.

214
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:21,919
Look again.

215
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,000
Look here.

216
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,159
I'm now

217
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,600
a lieutenant and Company Commander.

218
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,360
This old drunkard.

219
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,240
Your boy's an officer and you're unhappy.

220
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:39,279
The higher the rank,

221
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:40,799
the more they bully common folk.

222
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,240
How could I be like that?

223
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:45,440
How can you guarantee you won't?

224
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:46,360
Master,

225
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:47,519
you can keep an eye on me.

226
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:49,840
And what if I die?

227
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,559
You're just arguing to be difficult.

228
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,759
How can he guarantee that?

229
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:55,080
If he joins his sister's unit,

230
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,519
then I'll believe

231
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,799
he won't bully the common folk.

232
00:09:58,399 --> 00:09:58,879
Wherever I serve,

233
00:09:58,879 --> 00:09:59,720
I'm still a soldier.

234
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,519
It's different.

235
00:10:01,639 --> 00:10:02,480
How is it different?

236
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,879
He's drunk, just ignore him.

237
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,679
How is it different?

238
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,200
Here.

239
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:08,679
Take a look at this.

240
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,240
Come on.

241
00:10:09,679 --> 00:10:10,200
Look.

242
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,159
This is the book your sister reads.

243
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,799
Read it, and you'll see the difference.

244
00:10:16,919 --> 00:10:17,519
Master,

245
00:10:18,279 --> 00:10:19,360
this is a banned book.

246
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:19,840
So what?

247
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:20,960
Are you gonna arrest me?

248
00:10:22,679 --> 00:10:23,519
There's no reasoning with you.

249
00:10:23,879 --> 00:10:24,519
This book,

250
00:10:24,519 --> 00:10:25,440
I'm confiscating it.

251
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:27,240
Don't bring disaster to this family.

252
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,159
You're not eating?

253
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,080
No.

254
00:10:31,159 --> 00:10:31,799
I've got things to do.

255
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,399
Then come back and read it later.

256
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:33,679
Okay.

257
00:10:33,679 --> 00:10:34,960
Don't come back until you understand it.

258
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,200
If you keep this up,

259
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,279
I'll throw out your booze too.

260
00:10:38,519 --> 00:10:39,440
You're the one who spoils him.

261
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,159
What happened here?

262
00:11:00,879 --> 00:11:03,440
I heard the troops went to hunt bandits.

263
00:11:03,639 --> 00:11:04,559
From the looks of it,

264
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,080
they didn't fare too well.

265
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,600
Didn't you say

266
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,759
that holding a ghost marriage for my son

267
00:11:20,759 --> 00:11:22,200
and burying him in an auspicious spot

268
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,799
would bring me great fortune?

269
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,879
Now not only did the Communists escape,

270
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,840
they completely thrashed me.

271
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:32,600
Now look at this.

272
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,120
I lost half of my men.

273
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:37,000
Calm down, Brigade Commander.

274
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:39,679
You'll surely make a comeback.

275
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,320
Make a comeback?

276
00:11:43,159 --> 00:11:43,679
Me?

277
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,840
How can I possibly bounce back?

278
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,559
With what am I supposed to rise again?

279
00:11:49,279 --> 00:11:50,000
Money!

280
00:11:50,639 --> 00:11:52,960
With money, you'll never lack soldiers.

281
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,440
You just flap your lips together

282
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,320
and make it sound so easy.

283
00:11:58,799 --> 00:11:59,639
Where's the money?

284
00:12:00,159 --> 00:12:01,320
Where am I supposed to get it?

285
00:12:01,799 --> 00:12:02,840
In three days,

286
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:04,879
someone will surely deliver the money.

287
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,240
Really?

288
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,759
Absolutely certain.

289
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,159
Good.

290
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,000
I'll give you three days.

291
00:12:16,759 --> 00:12:17,840
Just rest and recover,

292
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,240
and wait for the good news.

293
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:29,600
Aunt Xiaoling.

294
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,240
What brings you here?

295
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:32,120
I heard you lost the battle.

296
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,440
Your Master was worried about you,

297
00:12:33,799 --> 00:12:34,919
